@node disclaimer "DISCLAIMER etc. LEGAL STUFF"
Epilepsy Warning
----------------

DO NOT, under any circumstances, run "Morning After Simulator" if you
suffer from epilepsy.  This contains rapidly flashing colours and could
cause a seizure even in people not known to be affected.

BE CAREFUL and, if in any doubt, DELETE IT!

Disclaimer
----------

We accept no responsibilty for anything which might possibly happen to your
computer if you, for example, leave it running while going to watch
Neighbours.  Or something inadvertantly reformats your hard drive.  Or
something else nasty occurs.  Come on - they've been tested enough to show
up nasty bugs, so nothing should happen, I'm just covering myself, OK?
Please note that the disclaimer also applies to the epilepsy warning above.

Did you know?  I've probably spent about a day simply typing disclaimers.

Other Information
-----------------

PLEASE DO NOT EXPECT ALL THE LINKS TO WORK!
This is an edited document, and I haven't checked or removed any links.

Also, do not expect everything mentioned to be on the disk.
@endnode

