@endnode

@node Find "Findit! - The file search jobbie"
@{u}Findit!@{uu} The file search program
@{i}By Chris Young 1996@{ui}

Please note: This requires at least WB3.0 (WB2.1 @{i}may @{ui}work, but I'm not sure if it has the relevant files...) and ARexx (active, of course - with the RX command available).  It also needs the following files to be available (ie. in the current search path(s)): Search RequestFile RequestChoice Delete MultiView (and the ascii.datatype etc...)

On loading, you will be presented with a file requestor.  Select the drawer/volume you wish to search, and type one of the following into the "filename" gadget:

· The name of a file to find - with standard AmigaDOS pattern-matching if you like.

· A string to search for within a file... PRECEDED WITH A DOLLAR SIGN ($)

· A string to search for, including pattern matching... PREFIXED WITH A PERCENTAGE SIGN (%)

Unfortunately, because you are typing the information into a file requestor, you can't search for strings containing colon (:) or slash (/) symbols.

Both of the bottom options require you to answer another request - do you want to show all the checked files/found text or not?

Yes: Show the files checked.  Any containing the appropiate string will show a portion of the file underneath.

No: Only the files containing the text will be shown.

After the search is completed, a MultiView window will appear with the relevant information.
@endnode

@node AcornROD "Random poem/song generators"
@{u}Random poem and song generators@{uu}
@{i}General program taken from the book "Practical Things to do with a Microcomputer"
Rod Hull poem by Chris Young and Phillip Lake, with ideas stolen from Fist of Fun.
