@node AmiROD "The Song and Poem Generator Compilation"
@{u}Random poem and song generators@{uu}
@{i}General program based on one from "Practical Things to do with a Microcomputer" (Osborne Publishing 1984)
Rod Hull poem by Chris Young and Phillip Lake, with ideas stolen from Fist of Fun.
Oasis Song Generator by Phillip Lake, from a program in PC Zone.
Whistlin' Rick Song Generator by Chris Young, with help from his song.@{ui}

@{b}This program requires ARexx and rexxsupport.library@{ub}
If it does not run, start ARexx by double-clicking on RexxMast in System.

Run the main program "Song&Poem" - a menu will appear.

1. Oasis Song

This wil randomly generate an Oasis song.  Type in a name (or whatever) to customise the song.

2. Whistlin' Rick Song

This generates Whistlin' Rick's latest song.

3. Rod Hull Poem

This randomly generates a poem about Rod Hull (sorry, but Emu does not feature in it).

4. Custom Song/Poem

This allows you to load in your own song/poem, created with @{"Custom_Song" link AmiROD.custom}.

It requires Arexx_ASL.library and ASL.library to be in libs:

When the file requestor appears, choose a file to load in (they end in @{b}.custom@{ub}).  There is a demonstration file included called "Original.custom", which is the original poem in the book.

5. This, and all subsequent lines, contain all the currently installed custom songs.  If the one you require does not feature, use option 4 to try and locate it.

14. More...

Moves onto the next page of custom songs, if it exists.
@endnode

@node AmiROD.custom "Custom_Song - generator thingy for Song&Poem"
@{u}Custom_Song for Song&Poem (The song and poem generator compilation)@{uu}
@{i}By Chris Young 1996@{ui}

Run the program Custom_Song (requires ARexx to be active), and a window will appear.  Follow the steps below to create your own random song/poem:

1. Enter the filename for this new song/poem (you do @{i}not@{ui} need to add the .custom suffix)

eg. » Amiga

2. Enter the name of this song/poem (it will stay in the same case)

eg. » The Amiga Song

3. Next, enter your name (this will stay in the case you enter it in)

eg. » Amiga Technologies GmbH

4. Type in each word you want to use in the song or poem (converted to caps)

eg. » AMIGA
    » KICKSTART
    » WORKBENCH
    » DISK
    » FLOPPY
    » HARD
    » IS
    » ROM
    » A
    » THE

5. When done, just press enter without typing anything.  The file will be saved.

6. Load Song&Poem, choosing the option marked "The Amiga Song" or option 4, selecting the file "Amiga.custom" from the file requestor.

7. Read the result:

THE AMIGA SONG (© 1996 Amiga Technologies GmbH)

ROM ROM DISK WORKBENCH
WORKBENCH HARD FLOPPY A A
WORKBENCH HARD AMIGA FLOPPY WORKBENCH
DISK DISK HARD HARD

DISK HARD ROM A
KICKSTART FLOPPY WORKBENCH DISK
A HARD WORKBENCH FLOPPY A
DISK A WORKBENCH DISK

IS FLOPPY KICKSTART FLOPPY IS
IS A FLOPPY DISK
DISK IS IS IS
FLOPPY A KICKSTART FLOPPY

I apologise to Amiga Tech. for copyrighting such a rubbish song to them.
@endnode

