@node 5t "The Technical Tory Think Tank"
@{u}The Technical Tory Think Tank (policy generator)@{uu}
@{i}By Chris Young/Unsatisfactory Software
Based on an idea by "The Friday Night Armistice"@{ui}

This generates a random policy (you won't understand a couple of them unless you know who the people are, but you could always load "5t.data" (Amiga) or the main program "5t" (Acorn) into a text editor and change the data into something you do understand).

After running a window appears with a new policy (wait or click to remove it).

I suggest that you put it into your WBStartup drawer (Amiga), !Boot.Tasks.PreDesk (or whereever it goes - RISC OS 3.5) or add it to the !Boot file (all Acorns) so you get a "policy of the day" when you boot up.
@endnode

@node Bloke "Big Matt's Bloke Joke Generator"
@{u}Big Matt's Bloke Joke Generator@{uu}
@{i}By Chris Young 1996
Based on a joke by Matthew McCann
(The icon is of Matthew himself, in case you're interested)@{ui}

Matthew ´Sigmond The Tree´ McCann once said to me, "I know a joke about everything".  Well, the only ones I heard were about members of the male population, so this Joke Generator is based on those.

After running (requires ARexx!) you will be presented with a window.  Simply type in the first name of a bloke, and a joke will be created based on the name you typed in.

The question appears... hit "Return" for the answer.
The entire joke is saved to the file "T:Joke" (T: is normally assigned to RAM:T), in case you want to, erm, use it in another program.  You could load it in to DPaint and make it look pretty, or something.
@endnode

