@node Barcode "Barcode Font"
@{u}Barcode Font - Creates Professional-looking Barcodes@{uu}

This font creates barcodes.  Well, that's it, really.

The font is generally mapped to numeric keys printing both line and number, @{i}shift@{ui}-ed keys printing just the bar and @{i}alt@{ui}-ed keys printing just the number.  This is for the British keymap, for other users consult the table below...

Bar and Number: 1 2 3 4 5 6 7 8 9 0

Bar (longer)  : ! " Ł $ % ^ & * ( )

Number only   : ą ˛ ł ˘ Ľ ˝ ľ · « »

You can also print a double "seperator" line by hitting the full stop key, and a little arrow with the greater than sign.

Please note that although this font is based on real barcodes, bars corresponding to numbers tend to vary slightly depending on where they are on the 'code - this font only has one bar type for each number, so may not necessarily correspond exactly to the number it is supposed to be representing when scanned with a barcode scanner.  I was going to go into Tesco and try a 'code out on their price checkpoint bit, but I haven't actually been in there recently, so haven't had chance.  Therefore I don't know how well this font fares in "the real world".

@{font Barcode,15}
Ľ.57532.793188.»
@font "Topaz.font",8
@endnode

