@node CRS "Random Cockney Rhyming Slang Generator"
@{u}Random Cockney Rhyming Slang Generator@{uu}
@{i}By Chris Young 1996@{ui}

Requires ARexx - as usual.

OK, so you can't think of any rhyming slang for "locker" (our favourite is currently "Jarvis Cocker"), so what do you do?  Well, obviously (since I'm writing about this program), you run CRS.  It'll ask you for the word you want, eg.

LOCKER

Then, after some disk accessing, it'll tell you something like:

TEAPOT ROCKER - LOCKER

and write this to a file "New Slang.logfile", which will be created if it doesn't exist.

Any words you type in are added to a list "CRS.data", which are used for the first word ("teapot" is used if the list is not found).

@{"Our fave home-made slang (and we didn't use this program, neither)" link Fave_Slang}
@endnode

@node Fave_Slang "Our fave home-made slang (and we didn't use this program, neither)"
